entries.title: At Least 1,600 Dead After Massive Earthquakes Rock The Middle East
entries.description: Thousands of people are feared dead in Turkey and Syria following two earthquakes that rocked the region on Monday. The 7.8-magnitude earthquake that struck shortly after 4 am was one of the strongest to hit Turkey over the last hundred years, leading to scores of buildings and homes being flattened into rubble. entries.title: Surfing Legend Bethany Hamilton Speaks Out On Allowing Trans Women To Compete Against Biological Women
entries.description: Surfing champion Bethany Hamilton spoke out over the weekend about the World Surf League’s new policy allowing transgender women to compete against biological females in the sport. entries.title: Dave Chappelle Wins Grammy Award For Netflix Special That Enraged Trans People
entries.description: Legendary comedian Dave Chappelle won a Grammy award on Sunday for best comedy album for his Netflix special “The Closer,” which sparked immense anger from leftists when it was released in October 2021. Chappelle’s win marks the fourth time he has won a Grammy. He was not in attendance at the event. Recording Academy CEO ...

entries.title: ‘Literally A Tribute To Satan’: Viewers Slam ‘Demonic’ Performance At The Grammys
